descript.purpose: Building Outlines based upon base imagery acquired by Pictometry in 2009. Building outlines delineated by Pictometry International Corp. in 2009.
descript.supplinf: Outlines based on the information visible in the vertical aerial photos. In the downtown area, building outlines will either be modified versions of the 2005 outlines or created directly from 2009 imagery. Due to the height of the buildings in the downtown region, building lean in the tiles will make it difficult to create accurate building outlines. The accuracy of the building outlines in the downtown area cannot be guaranteed.

idinfo.useconst: User is responsible for any applied use.

metainfo.metstdn: FGDC Content Standards for Digital Geospatial Metadata

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Each building outline is associated to the parcel in which the geographic center is located. These are King County Parcel Identification Numbers (PIN) at the time of the building outline delination.
The X value of the geographic center of the outline polygon.
The Y value of the geographic center of the outline polygon.
Spatial extent of polygon in map units (feet).

This number shows whether the building outline was modified from the existing 2005 outline or created solely off the 2009 imagery. Zero(0) means the building outline was created from 2009 imagery, one(1) means the building outline was modified from the 2005 outline.
Spatial extent of polygon in map units (feet).
Length of polygon outline in map units (feet).

horizpa.horizpar: Positional Accuracy: offset from the imagery less than equal to 5 pixels Geometric Accuracy: length of untraced edges less than equal to 5 pixels Error Rate: ratio of positionally/geometrically inaccurate buildings and missed buildings less than equal to 0.5%
